Aren’t they trying to lower infections?  Just a guess but having an open border probably isn’t going to help with that…

node.text: Apparently #HunterBiden suddenly discovered his artistic side, right after his dad became President. Time to milk this thing as much as possible knowing the media will barely touch the issue. Imagine if #DonaldTrumpJr started to sell paintings to unknown individuals for large sums of cash while his dad was #POTUS. I wonder if the media would care. 🤨 Well, since he’s the son of a prominent establishment Democrat, most of the media just shrugs and asks when the art show is. That my friends, is true privilege right there, and if is enjoyed by prominent Democrat politicians and their families. #WheresHunter ? Well, he’s an arTIST now and he’s willing to sell you his art if you can hook him up with some cash or another kushy no-show job he’s not qualified for. Everyone should absolutely demand all of those “Art deals” are 100% transparent, but we know it probably won’t happen. #SleepyJoe will just shrug and deflect it, if he’s even asked, just like he did during the election.  It’s pretty sad that our media is 95% one sided and biased beyond comprehension. Isn’t that how it is in China and North Korea? 🤔 👏🏼 #comeonman #sleepyjoe #cnn #obama #barackobama #democrats

node.title: Former Obama Ethics Director on Hunter Biden Selling his “Art”

node.text:
#SanFrancisco Police: 

“We’ve seen a rise in violent attacks by homeless individuals, including attacks on #policeofficers. We are deeply grateful to these citizens who rushed to our officer’s aide. Our staffing shortage left this officer working alone instead of with a partner.” 

Everyone should be thankful to police officers for everything they have to deal with, including mentally ill individuals living on the street — all while leftists want to defund or abolish them.  What a “woke” joke. 

#bluelivesmatter #backtheblue #backtheblue💙 #lawenforcement

node.title: Homeless Man Attacks Short-Staffed Female Police Officer, Citizens Help 💙

node.text:
#CNN “reporter” asks #KarenFann — #Arizona State Senator who is conducting an audit of the 2020 election in her state. Watch as the CNN reporter (and then the anchors) fight aggressively to convince themselves that potential fraud should not be investigated. If they were reporting on #DonaldTrump’s second term I’ll bet they would be extremely interested in potential fraud. They also took shots at OAN. 

“Are you saying that #OAN is not a credible news source?”

CNN Reporter: “YASSS.” 

… Saying OAN is not credible is pretty funny coming from CNN …

node.title: CNN Confronts AZ State Senator in Charge of Election Audit in Arizona

node.text:
I like this guy. He makes a good case for how “stupid” politicians (and there are too many of them) squander and misuse money they collect from taxpayers. I would be less irritated by big spending if I knew that most of it would actually go towards said projects. But most of the time politicians use that money to enrich themselves or their families through various “administrative” costs. That’s political speak for hiring their friends and family to share the wealth while us peasants pay for it. Spending a lot is usually irresponsible, but what makes it worse is how that money gets wasted and the “projects” they say they’ll work on don’t get completed or take 10 times longer than initially promised. Best example I can think of is high speed rail in CA, which has been a sad joke on CA taxpayers. Sadly those taxpayers just keep voting for the same politicians so maybe they’re okay with their money being wasted. That or they get all their news from
CNN / MSNBC. 🤷🏻‍♂️

node.title: Countries Go Into Debt because of “Ridiculous Ineffective Politicians”

node.text:
The same Democrats who want to defund the police are spending hundreds of thousands of dollars (of your tax payer money) on private security to protect themselves. Democrat Rep. #CoriBush defends hiring private security for herself, while also trying to get rid of security for you:

“Suck it up. Defunding the police needs to happen.” … so basically, her message to you is HER life is worth defending but YOURS isn’t. 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 She has important work to do, but you do NOT … What are your thoughts on that? Isn’t she lovely? Congrats #Missouri on electing this fine politician to represent you. Why doesn’t Cori defund her private security and put that money into a social safety net? 🤔 Naw?  I get that politicians need security, but so does the public. Apparently not according to a lot of Democrats. How does any of that make sense? #lawenforcement #defundthepolice #backtheblue #backtheblue💙 #hypocrisy
